The paper primarily focuses on the security challenges and requirements of remote OTA updates in vehicles, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the integration of OTA update features with connected car technology, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SY) and embedded systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the benefits of OTA updates for cars, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.CY). Finally, the paper provides a classification of existing works in literature, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
